    <pre wrap="">Any such feature would need to be optional because it 
essentially means storing every deleted message for every 
local account for a pre-determined amount of time. For large 
sites, the storage requirement for this could be huge. 
Perhaps an option to limit the size of "recovery storage" 
would help, but then if one user deleted that amount of space 
at once, all other users would lose their recovery option if 
the recovery storage were shared.

Such an option would have to work with MAPI or maybe webmail. 
Somehow the server would have to store the account name in an 
index so a user could "undo" his delete action without you 
having to review all the messages in the recovery file. 
Either that or keep a separate recovery file for each user 
that had a separate storage limit from his regular account. 
I'm sure it could be done. Whether Stalker thinks it's a 
worthwhile feature to add is another matter.

Bret

